  {
    "id": "f_csv_e3f502a3d8",
    "slug": "my-mother-s-dad-dropped-out-of-the-eighth-grade-to-work-he-had-to-by-the-time",
    "texto": "My mother's dad dropped out of the eighth grade to work. He had to. By the time he was 30, he was a master electrician, plumber, carpenter, mason, mechanic. That guy was, to me, a magician. Anything that was broken, he could fix. Anybody anywhere in our community knew that if there was a problem, Carl was there to fix it.",
